The paper is primarily concerned with the design and analysis of algorithms for minimizing finite automata, which is a topic in formal language theory (FL) and data structures (DS). The paper also mentions applications in text processing and linguistic computer science, which are areas of natural language processing (CL). The paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (IT) and machine learning (LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.FL and cs.DS, followed by cs.LG, cs.IT, and cs.CL.
